dc_description_s:
Link to the DNR web page with information about PRESTO and PRESTO-lite and links to the tools.  The Pollutant Load Ratio Estimation Tool (PRESTO) is a statewide GIS-based tool that compares the average annual phosphorus loads originating from point and nonpoint sources within a watershed.                                 The comparison provides a screening tool for industrial and municipal dischargers to determine one of the conditions of eligibility for adaptive management as part of s. NR 217.18, Wisconsin Administrative Code.

*to download this
item from the DNR Open Data Portal, simply visit
the item and your browser will automatically prompt you to download it.
